nodes.name: ReserveImpl

attributes.name: ReserveImpl

devdoc.details: This contract should be used an implementation contract for an AdminUpgradeabilityProxy

admin().return: Address of the current proxy admin contract

borrow(address,uint256).details: Non-reentrant     Caller must be owner     Used to pre-fund trusted contracts with ESD without backing (e.g. batchers)

params.account: Address to send the borrowed ESD to

claimVault().details: Owner only - governance hook     Claims COMP accrued from lending on the USDC pool

delegateVault(address,address).details: Owner only - governance hook     Works for all COMP-based governance tokens

params.delegatee: Account to receive reserve's voting power
params.token: Governance token to delegate voting power

mint(uint256).details: Non-reentrant     Normalizes for decimals     Caller must approve reserve to transfer USDC

mintStake(address,uint256).details: Non-reentrant     Owner only - governance hook     ESDS maxes out at ~79b total supply (2^96/10^18) due to its 96-bit limitation     Will revert if totalSupply exceeds this maximum

params.makerToken: Token that the reserve wishes to sell
params.takerToken: Token that the reserve wishes to buy

redeem(uint256).details: Non-reentrant     Normalizes for decimals     Caller must approve reserve to transfer ESD

redeemPrice().details: Returned as a Decimal.D256     Normalizes for decimals (e.g. 1.00 USDC == Decimal.one())     Equivalent to the current reserve ratio less the current redemption tax (if any)

params.amount: Amount of the makerToken that reserve wishes to sell - uint256(-1) indicates all reserve funds
params.makerToken: Token that the reserve wishes to sell
params.price: Price as a ratio of takerAmount:makerAmount times 10^18
params.takerToken: Token that the reserve wishes to buy

registry().return: Address of the current registry contract

params.account: Address to repay ESD on behalf of

reserveRatio().details: Assumes 1 ESD = 1 USDC, normalizing for decimals

setRegistry(address).details: Owner only - governance hook     If registry is already set, the new registry's timelock must match the current's

setup().details: Governance hook     Does not ensure that it is only called once because it is permissioned to governance only

swap(address,address,uint256).details: Non-reentrant     Uses the state-defined price for the `makerToken`-`takerToken` order     Maker and taker tokens must be different     Cannot swap ESD

params.makerToken: Token that the caller wishes to buy
params.takerToken: Token that the caller wishes to sell

takeOwnership().details: Needs to be called initialize ownership after deployment     Ensure that this has been properly set before using the protocol
